history.content:
Question 1: Yes, it will fulfill both

Question 2: Yes, 12 units are required. You should speak with your ESS Adviser to see if they will approve 11 units given that you work park time (I think it has to be 15+ hours and paid). If you receive financial aid, are an international student, or a student athlete, you will need to check with the respective office as aid/visas/ncaa eligibility can be revoked under 12 units. Worst case, take a DeCal or seminar.

Hi,

I am a junior transfer EECS major and I was wondering if BioE100 will count as both an upper division H/SS and fulfill my ethics requirement? My other upper division H/SS was an AC, so after this I should be done this requirement as a whole?

Also, are we required to take 12 units? Next semester I will be in 61c, upper division EECS, and perhaps BioE100, which puts me at 11. I planned on enrolling in another course, but given that it will happen in Phase II, I want to know if I am unable to take another course (I also work part time), will 11 be okay?

Thank you.
